{"id":6473780,"date":"2024-10-23T12:30:00","date_gmt":"2024-10-23T07:00:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/?p=6473780"},"modified":"2025-09-04T16:48:00","modified_gmt":"2025-09-04T11:18:00","slug":"10-best-career-options-after-mca-degree","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/10-best-career-options-after-mca-degree","title":{"rendered":"10 best career options after MCA degree"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>An MCA degree is one of the ideal course choices for students looking to advance in a career in computer technology. The course equips students with specialized technical skills and presents many career opportunities. In this blog, we will discuss the different <strong>career options after MCA<\/strong> degree completion. Online Manipal offers online MCA to help build your professional career in the domain.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Career options after MCA<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As stated above, graduation from MCA can unlock numerous career prospects. This section details some of the top <strong>job opportunities after MCA <\/strong>that you can apply for:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">1. System Architect<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A System Architect is responsible for designing and maintaining complex computer systems. They should ensure that the company website can handle visitors. They have a good understanding of hardware and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/12-best-accounting-software-and-tools-for-bcom-mcom-students\">software<\/a> components to ensure that the system architecture aligns with the company\u2019s requirements.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Roles and responsibilities&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Analyze the hardware and software requirements of the company<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Plan and implement upgrades&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Create backup plans in case of a system crash<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Important skills needed<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Good communication skills<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Knowledge of computer systems and programming languages<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Knowledge of coding&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Average annual pay of System Architect in India:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/system-architect-salary-SRCH_KO0,16.htm\">INR 12 lakh &#8211; INR 30.8 lakh per annum<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">2. Cloud Architect<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>These IT professionals help design and manage the cloud infrastructure of a company. They also deal with service providers such as Amazon Web Services (AWS), Google Cloud Platform (GCP), Microsoft Azure, and others.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Roles and responsibilities&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Help in designing the cloud architecture&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Help in building network security by implementing <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/cybersecurity-essentials-for-bca-mca-students\">security protocols<\/a> and monitoring for threats<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Develop and execute migration strategies<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Important skills needed&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Knowledge of cloud computing platforms<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Problem-solving mentality and identifying underlying causes of an issue<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Strong decision-making abilities to help prioritize tasks and manage the team<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Average annual pay of Cloud Architect in India:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/cloud-architect-salary-SRCH_KO0,15.htm#:~:text=The%20average%20salary%20for%20Cloud%20Architect%20is%20%E2%82%B923%2C39%2C598,%E2%82%B93%2C60%2C000%2C%20with%20a%20range%20from%20%E2%82%B93%2C60%2C000%20-%20%E2%82%B93%2C60%2C000.\">INR 10 lakh &#8211; INR 27 lakh per annum<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">3. IT Project Manager<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An Information Technology (IT) Project Manager is responsible for leading projects and software development. They help achieve IT targets set by the company to achieve their goals. They lead multiple IT projects and communicate with vendors and executive leaders.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Roles and responsibilities&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Handle multiple IT projects<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Gather and analyze IT metrics<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Introduce new software solutions&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Important skills needed&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Communication and leadership skills to manage the team<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Knowledge of computers and technology&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Time-management skills<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Average annual pay of IT Project Manager in India:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/it-project-manager-salary-SRCH_KO0,18.htm\">INR 10 lakh &#8211; INR 22 lakh per annum<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">4. Data Scientist<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A Data Scientist or Data Analyst helps business organizations by converting raw data into useful information, thereby improving their business. They are experts in machine learning and have good knowledge of computer programming languages.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Roles and responsibilities&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Analyzing raw and unstructured data<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Converting big data into data sets<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Simplifying data into actionable insights for stakeholders<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Important skills needed&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Good verbal and written communication skills<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Knowledge of algorithms and computer languages&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ability to visualize and present data<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Average annual pay of Data Scientist in India:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/data-scientist-salary-SRCH_KO0,14.htm\">INR 7 lakh &#8211; INR 20 lakh per annum<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">5. AI\/ML Engineer<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An Artificial Intelligence (AI) or Machine Learning (ML) Engineer creates AI models using engineering and programming knowledge to perform and improve tasks.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Roles and responsibilities&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Creating and maintaining AI infrastructure&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Converting AI models into Application Program Interfaces (APIs)&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Decoding the results from <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/stay-relevant-in-the-age-of-artificial-intelligence\">AI models<\/a> and conveying them to the stakeholders<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Important skills needed<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Proficiency in programming languages&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Good communication skills to explain complex data in simple language&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Good understanding of ML algorithms&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Average annual pay of an AI\/ML Engineer in India:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/ai-ml-engineer-salary-SRCH_KO0,14.htm\">INR 6 lakh &#8211; INR 15 lakh per annum<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">6. Software Developer\/Engineer<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A Software Engineer is an IT professional who uses programming languages to develop software solutions. They design and research new software programs. They also help manage software releases, address issues with the software, and help with troubleshooting.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Roles and responsibilities<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Developing and testing a system or application<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updating the system and handling fixes<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Upgrading software for existing systems<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Important skills needed&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Able to work as a team with technical as well as non-technical members<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Able to use various programming languages, such as Java, C++, Python, and others<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Able to pay attention to detail while fixing an issue<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Average annual pay of Software Engineer in India:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/software-engineer-salary-SRCH_KO0,17.htm#:~:text=Software%20Engineer%20Salaries%20in%20India&amp;text=The%20average%20salary%20for%20Software,29%2C100%20%2D%20%E2%82%B92%2C00%2C000.\">INR 5 lakh &#8211; 15 lakh per annum<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">7. Database Administrator (DBA)<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A DBA is responsible for maintaining the overall performance and ensuring the security of a company\u2019s database. They also back up data and provide training to users. There are different types of DBAs, such as System Administrators, Database Architects, Database Analysts, Performance Analysts, and Data Modelers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Roles and responsibilities&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Installation and testing of new <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/database-management-jobs\">database management<\/a> systems&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Develop and maintain backup plans<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ensuring database security<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Important skills needed&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Excellent communication skills with team members<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Good understanding of business and IT requirements&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Problem-solving ability<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Average annual pay of DBA in India:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/database-administrator-salary-SRCH_KO0,22.htm\">INR 5 lakh &#8211; INR 11.6 lakh per annum<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">8. Full Stack Developer<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>They help in building the front-end and back-end of a website. They are generally responsible for designing and creating websites. The front end of the website is visible and accessible to users, while the back-end is used to store data.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Roles and responsibilities&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Helps in developing and maintaining web services<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Develops and maintains the front-end and back-end of the website<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Helps with troubleshooting and fixing bugs<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Important skills needed&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Good knowledge of programming languages, such as Python, PHP, etc.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ability to design and maintain databases<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Attention to detail<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Average annual pay of a Full Stack Developer in India:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/full-stack-developer-salary-SRCH_KO0,20.htm\">INR 4 lakh &#8211; INR 11 lakh per annum<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">9. Cybersecurity Analyst\/Expert<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A Cybersecurity Analyst is responsible for protecting the company\u2019s computer networks from unauthorized access and threats. They help keep the company\u2019s data secure from threats by implementing security protocols, upgrading systems, and installing antivirus software.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Roles and responsibilities&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Maintaining antivirus software<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Implementing security measures<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Investigating security alerts<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Important skills needed<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Good communication skills to ensure safety practices are followed in case of an event<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Critical thinking skills to help deal with a cybersecurity incident<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Good knowledge of data security and network security<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Average annual pay of Cybersecurity Analyst in India:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/india-cyber-security-analyst-salary-SRCH_IL.0,5_IN115_KO6,28.htm\">INR 4 lakh &#8211; INR 10 lakh per annum<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">10. DevOps Engineer<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>DevOps Engineers are professionals with knowledge of both software development and IT operations. They are responsible for working with both the development and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-operations-management\">operations<\/a> teams to ensure quick and secure delivery of software.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Roles and responsibilities&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Ensuring the successful development and deployment of software&nbsp;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Implementing continuous integration and delivery (CI\/CD) pipelines to allow for quick software releases<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ensuring company data is safe and secure<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Important skills needed&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Problem-solving skills<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Excellent management skills to handle different teams<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Knowledge of system architecture and system administration&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Average annual pay of DevOps Engineer in India:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.simplilearn.com\/devops-engineer-salary-in-india-article#:~:text=For%20entry%2Dlevel%20DevOps%20engineers%20with%200%2D2%20years,INR%204%20to%208%20lakhs%20per%20annum.\">INR 4 lakhs to INR 8 lakhs per annum<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Pursue online MCA with Online Manipal<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Manipal University Jaipur (MUJ) offers an online MCA program that can be completed from the comfort of your home. This two-year course is divided into four semesters. You need to invest around 15-20 hours per week and the remaining time can be used for pursuing a job or other personal commitments. This degree is globally recognized by <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/what-are-the-top-government-jobs-for-bca-graduates-in-india\">governments<\/a> and organizations to give you the freedom to work anywhere.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Manipal University Jaipur is Rajasthan\u2019s first NAAC A+ accredited university. It also secured the 13th rank in India\u2019s top 15 management universities in 2023. Its <strong>online MCA degree program<\/strong> allows students exclusive access to Coursera where you can choose from 10,000+ courses and professional certifications from global universities to help you build a strong professional career.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You will also benefit from access to 110+ hours from the Online Manipal Skills Academy to enhance your <strong>skills after your MCA degree<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are unlimited <strong>job opportunities after completing an MCA<\/strong> degree. You can get jobs in reputed companies, such as Infosys, Tata Consultancy Services (TCS), Accenture, Wipro, and HCL Technologies, among others.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>online MCA degree program<\/strong> is in high demand due to global digitalization. You need various specialized <strong>skills after an MCA degree,<\/strong> such as effective communication, leadership, problem-solving ability, analytical thinking, and time management to be successful in your career.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Online Manipal offers you the option of getting a professional <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/\">degree online<\/a> from the comfort of your home. Sign up for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mca-degree-muj\">online MCA<\/a> on the platform through Manipal University Jaipur and take the first step to a globally successful career path in the world of IT.\u00a0<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>An MCA degree is one of the ideal course choices for students looking to advance in a career in computer technology. The course equips students with specialized technical skills and presents many career opportunities. In this blog, we will discuss the different career options after MCA degree completion. Online Manipal offers online MCA to help [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":19,"featured_media":5763863,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[607],"tags":[37],"class_list":["post-6473780","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-mca","tag-online-education-in-india"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v27.5 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/product\/yoast-seo-wordpress\/ -->\n<title>10 best career options after MCA degree - Online Manipal<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"An overview of the 10 best career options after completing an MCA degree with roles and responsibilities and skill needed.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6473780\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_GB\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"10 best career options after MCA degree - Online Manipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"An overview of the 10 best career options after completing an MCA degree with roles and responsibilities and skill needed.\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/10-best-career-options-after-mca-degree\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"Online Manipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:publisher\" content=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/onlinemanipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:published_time\" content=\"2024-10-23T07:00:00+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:modified_time\" content=\"2025-09-04T11:18:00+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/Job-related-1.jpg\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:width\" content=\"706\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:height\" content=\"395\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:type\" content=\"image\/jpeg\" \/>\n<meta name=\"author\" content=\"Editorial Team\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary_large_image\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:label1\" content=\"Written by\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:data1\" content=\"Editorial Team\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:label2\" content=\"Estimated reading time\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:data2\" content=\"7 minutes\" \/>\n<script type=\"application\/ld+json\" class=\"yoast-schema-graph\">{\"@context\":\"https:\\\/\\\/schema.org\",\"@graph\":[{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/10-best-career-options-after-mca-degree\",\"url\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/10-best-career-options-after-mca-degree\",\"name\":\"10 best career options after MCA degree - Online Manipal\",\"isPartOf\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/#website\"},\"primaryImageOfPage\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/10-best-career-options-after-mca-degree#primaryimage\"},\"image\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/blogs\\\/10-best-career-options-after-mca-degree#primaryimage\"},\"thumbnailUrl\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipal.com\\\/wp-content\\\/uploads\\\/2024\\\/10\\\/Job-related-1.jpg\",\"datePublis